{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Ricotta","content":["Place milk into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>15 min\/80°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add vinegar and heat <nobr>7 min\/90°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Allow to sit in mixing bowl for 2 minutes. Milk will separate into curds and whey.","Line simmering basket with 2 layers of muslin cloth or a nut milk bag and set over a large bowl. Pour mixture into simmering basket and allow to drain for 30 minutes. Do not squeeze liquid from ricotta. Set drained ricotta (approx. 300-340 g) aside in a bowl. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Grain free crackers","content":["Place a small bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh chia seeds and water into it. Set bowl aside for 1 hour.","Preheat oven to 170°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and set aside.","Place almonds, sunflower seeds, linseeds, sea salt flakes, granulated garlic and chilli flakes into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved soaked chia seed mixture and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Place 1 large piece of baking paper onto work surface and pour mixture onto baking paper. Top with another large sheet of baking paper and roll out mixture to approx. 2-3 mm thickness. Remove top sheet of baking paper and sprinkle with sesame seeds and additional sea salt flakes, and press down gently.","Using a knife or pizza cutter, cut dough into triangles, transfer onto prepared baking trays and bake for 15-20 minutes (170°C), or until golden brown. Leave to cool on baking trays for 5 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.","Increase oven temperature to 180°C. Clean and dry mixing bowl.."]},{"title":"Baked ricotta","content":["Grease a ramekin (10-15 cm) or other small baking dish and set aside.","Place Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add all remaining ingredients, including reserved ricotta, and mix <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer into prepared ramekin or baking dish and bake for 25-30 minutes (180°C), or until set and golden brown. Serve baked ricotta hot with grain free crackers."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Ricotta","content":["1800 g full cream milk","80 g white vinegar"]},{"title":"Grain free crackers","content":["30 g chia seeds","120 g water","280 g raw almonds","60 g sunflower seeds","30 g linseeds","1 tsp sea salt flakes","1 tsp granulated garlic","½ - 1 tsp dried chilli flakes","sea salt flakes, for sprinkling","30 g sesame seeds"]},{"title":"Baked ricotta","content":["oil, for greasing","120 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into pieces (3 cm)","1 egg","2 - 3 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","½ tsp dried chilli flakes","1 - 2 pinches salt","1 - 2 pinches ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r97488","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-jsYCjOmpYG0\/XZafk8u_M6I\/AAAAAAAAgvw\/etLaFi8A5PoLMpOdEDPVe8IGYLXabbBkgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rXlfDmMs-6SV48c3.png","title":"Savoury herb baked ricotta","publishedAt":"2016-09-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"24.96 g","fat":"42.367 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"16.867 g","calories":"2323 kJ \/ 553 kcal"},"usefulItems":"nut milk bag or muslin cloth, large bowl, bowl, small bowl, baking trays, baking paper, rolling pin, pizza cutter, wire rack, ramekin (10 - 15 cm), oven","basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 40m","8 portions"]}